Executive Profile
Errol   Ginsberg  Chairman of the Board and Chief Innovation Officer, IxiaAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships61$1,520,011As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Errol Ginsberg serves as the Chief Innovation Officer at Anue Systems, Inc. Mr. Ginsberg founded Ixia in 1997 and has been its Chief Innovation Officer since March 2008. Mr. Ginsberg serves as Chairman of Ixia since January 2008. He served as an Acting Chief Executive Officer of Anue Systems, Inc. He leads the newly formed Ixia Labs and responsible for advanced engineering to help drive organic growth in new product areas. He served as an Acting Chief Executive Officer ... of Ixia since October 24, 2013 until September 16, 2014. He has 20 years of experience in the communications industry, with broad expertise in the design, development and successful commercial marketing of technologies for the Internet and distributed networking community. He served as the President of Ixia from May 1997 to September 2007 and also as its Chief Executive Officer from September 2000 to March 2008. He overseen many of Ixia's innovations, including multiuser high-density platforms, CPU per-port interface modules and high-productivity, test-specific applications, where he helped shape the IP communications testing industry. Before Ixia, he served as vice president of Engineering at NetVantage. From November 1994 to February 1996, he served as an engineering consultant to Netcom Systems. He has been the Chairman of Anue Systems, Inc. since January 2008. He serves as a Director at QuorumLabs, Inc. He has been a Director of Catapult Communications Corporation. since June 2009. Mr. Ginsberg served as an Executive Director of Ixia since May 1997 until April 18, 2017. Mr. Ginsberg holds a BSEE from the University of Witwatersrand in South Africa.Read Full Background




